Give a brief history of the internet (1985-present)
The internet began in 1969 as a project sponsored by the US Department of Defense to connect computers over long distances. The first internet protocol, called the 'Arpanet', was developed by computer scientist Robert Kahn in 1969. The internet has since evolved into a global network, connecting millions of users and devices. Significant developments include the introduction of the World Wide Web in 1991, the development of HTML and JavaScript in 1993, and the rise of social media platforms in the 2000s.

Some good coding practices include: 

1. Using descriptive variable names to make the code more readable.
2. Using comments to explain what the code does.
3. Separating code into functions to make it easier to maintain.
4. Using consistent naming conventions for variables and functions.
5. Using a consistent coding style to make the code more consistent.
6. Testing code thoroughly to ensure it works as intended.
7. Using version control systems to keep track of changes in the code.
8. Using comments to explain what the code does.
9. Using consistent naming conventions for variables and functions.
10. Using a consistent coding style to make the code more consistent.
